	,"x4codes":[{"code":"VDG", "dict":"FACILITY", "idict":18,"hlp":"Van de Graaff"}
	    ,{"code":"2GERBER", "dict":"INSTITUTE", "idict":3,"hlp":"Hahn-Meitner-Inst., Berlin, Germany"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" the 5.5 MV Van de Graaff generator"]
	}
      ]
     ,"DETECTOR":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4codes":[{"code":"SCIN", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Scintillation detector"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" The neutrons emitted in the reaction were"
		,"detected simultaneously by one detector at a fixed"
		,"angle for monitoring purposes and six movable"
		,"detectors-NE213 liquid scintillators of 10.2 cm in"
		,"diameter and 2.5 cm thickness."]
	}
      ]
     ,"COMMENT":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["*By authors*.In order to extract angular distributions"
		,"of the measured spectra the relative efficiency of the"
		,"detectors has to be calibrated and their volume and"
		,"threshold energy for the detection of neutrons is then"
		,"determined. The threshold was measured from the"
		,"bombardment of a thick stainless steel target. Thus"
		,"the threshold shows up directly in the measured  time-"
		,"of-flight spectrum and can be determined with an"
		,"accuracy of +-30 keV. The time-of-flight spectrum  of"
		,"Be-9(d,n) was used to calibrate the time scale."]
	}
      ]
